Factor the formula into a helper:
```rust
fn resolve_effective_runner(
    ctx: &IterationContext,
    task_id: &str,
    effective_model: Option<&str>,
) -> RunnerKind {
    ctx.runner_overrides.get(task_id).copied().unwrap_or_else(|| {
        match provider_for_model(effective_model) {
            Provider::Grok => RunnerKind::Grok,
            Provider::Claude => RunnerKind::Claude,
        }
    })
}
```
Call it at both sites. Helper lives in engine.rs or runner.rs (caller's choice; prefer engine.rs to keep runner.rs free of IterationContext coupling).

